article.description: No. 11 Baylor drops past Texas-Pan American 96-42
article.headline: No. 11 Baylor drops past Texas-Pan American 96-42
article.linkText: No. 11 Baylor drops past Texas-Pan American 96-42
article.story:
WACO, Texas --  Nina Davis hit 13 of 15 shots and scored 23 of her 31 points in the first half as No. 11 Baylor cruised to a 96-42 win over Pan American on Wednesday night.

Khadijiah Cave added 18 points, Kristina Higgins had 15 and Imani Wright 11 for the Bears (5-1). Niya Johnson had 10 assists.

The Broncos (6-4) have lost four road games against ranked teams.

Baylor shot 56.7 percent (38-67) for the game -- despite Wright going 2 of 12 -- with Cave hitting 8 of 10 shots and Higgins 7 of 9.

Pan American shot 26.5 percent, was out-rebounded 52-36 and had 20 turnovers.

Pan American had a 12-11 lead when Davis scored nine straight points to start Baylor on an 18-0 run. The Bears stretched the lead to 54-22 at the half.

Cave had 12 of her points in the second half as the Bears coasted.
